# React + TypeScript standards (apps/web)

Complements `web-frontend.mdc` (feature structure + boundary). These are the quality rules.

## Components
- **Functional components only** (hooks); no class components.
- Type props with **interfaces**; components named in **PascalCase**.
- Extract **custom hooks** for complex/reusable logic; keep components presentational.
- Implement **error boundaries**; follow **atomic design** (atoms → molecules → organisms).

## State & data
- **React Query** for all server state / data fetching; no manual fetch-in-effect for server data.
- Implement **optimistic updates** where it improves UX.
- **No prop drilling beyond 2 levels** — use context or composition instead.

## Localization (required)
- **No hardcoded user-facing strings** in components. All labels go through the i18n layer
  (e.g. `t('projects.create.title')`); support multiple languages + locale formatting (dates,
  numbers) — and store/compare timestamps in UTC.

## Testing
- **100% test coverage** (Vitest); descriptive test names; cover loading/error/empty states.

```tsx
// ❌ const title = 'Create project';
// ✅ const title = t('projects.create.title');
```
